neruniface_104kly1665702735187.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kly1665702735187.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kly1665702735187.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kly1665702735187\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      tds_packetsize\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Set the Sybase packet size.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"kly1665702735187__topic_d59999e1_d60000e1_d60001e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kly1665702735187__p_d60002e1_d60003e1_d60004e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">USYS$SYS_PARAMS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">tds_packetsize</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kly1665702735187__section_zcz_bww_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1148574e66\">Arguments</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kly1665702735187__p_d60008e1_d60009e1_d60010e1\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>— integer that is a multiple\n            of 512</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kly1665702735187__section_xt1_dww_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1148574e77\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kly1665702735187__p_d60014e1_d60015e1_d60016e1\">This option can change the performance of the\n            connector in either a positive or a negative way.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kly1665702735187__p_d60017e1_d60018e1_d60019e1\">When using this option, you need to ensure that the\n            Sybase SQL server can handle the packet size. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"glt1665702968317.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/glt1665702968317.html\">Set the Sybase Packet Size</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kly1665702735187__p_d60020e1_d60021e1_d60022e1\">If this connector option is not specified, the default\n            Sybase server packet size is used.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529268\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529268\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "tds_packetsize Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 tds_packetsize Set the Sybase packet size. USYS$SYS_PARAMS tds_packetsize Value Arguments Value — integer that is a multiple of 512 Description This option can change the performance of the connector in either a positive or a negative way. When using this option, you need to ensure that the Sybase SQL server can handle the packet size. For more information, see Set the Sybase Packet Size . If this connector option is not specified, the default Sybase server packet size is used. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}